title: M-E named grand champs in STAC cheer competition
text:
M-E named grand champs in STAC cheer competition 
By WBNG News October 25, 2015 Updated Oct 25, 2015 at 7:00 PM EDT 
Endicott, NY (WBNG Binghamton) It was a packed house Sunday at Union-Endicott High School for a STAC cheerleading competition. 
This is the second year U-E hosted the event. 
WBNG E-News - Sign Up For Our Newsletter! 
Sixteen high schools from around the Southern Tier were there to show off their school spirit. Maine-Endwell's varsity team was the grand champs of the competition. 
Even though the U-E varsity cheer squad didn't take home first place, they said they still had fun representing the tigers. 
"It's nerve racking, but us being the host, this is new. This is only the second year that we've done this," said U-E Varsity cheerleader Sierra Babcock. "It's really cool being here at our gym, we really have to represent."
